    <stitle>13 SPEED AND 18 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO-713/18 SERIES - INSTALL - COUNTERSHAFT BEARINGS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="5">
        <title>COUNTERSHAFT BEARINGS</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Move the countershaft to the rear and insert the countershaft support tool to center the
                shaft in the rear case bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007m1">Figure 221</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13007m1" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13007m1" filename="../figg13/G13007M1.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 221. Move Countershaft to Rear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a flanged-end driver to start the front bearing in the case bore.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a screwdriver inserted in the countershaft bolt bore to help center the countershaft.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Move the countershaft forward into the bearing.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a flanged-end bearing driver and maul to completely seat the front bearing in the case
                bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007m2">Figure 222</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13007m2" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13007m2" filename="../figg13/G13007M2.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 222. Seat Front Bearing in Case Bore</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position the retainer plate with roll pin in the shaft end hole on the countershaft front (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007m3">Figure 223</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13007m3" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13007m3" filename="../figg13/G13007M3.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 223. Secure Retainer Plate With Bolt</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Secure with a bolt and tighten to 90 to 120 ft-lbs. (122 to 163 N&#183;m) (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007m3">Figure 223</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the countershaft support tool from the rear.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With the larger I.D. lead chamfer to the shaft front, use a flanged-end bearing driver and
                install the rear bearing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007m4">Figure 224</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13007m4" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13007m4" filename="../figg13/G13007M4.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 224. Install Rear Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the rear snap ring in the countershaft rear groove (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007m5">Figure 225</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13007m5" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13007m5" filename="../figg13/G13007M5.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 225. Install Rear Snap Ring Countershaft Rear Groove</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
